records.addlTxt: JOC corrected to amend the charges in counts 1, 2 and 3 (removing enhancers).

ADDRESS INFO for Cyanne L. Tracy
Current: 6506 County Road B, Manitowoc, WI 54220 United States  (Effective: 11-02-2022)
Prior: Manitowoc County Jail, Manitowoc, WI 54220 United States

Defendant Cyanne L. Tracy in court.  Attorney Daniel G. Mitchell in court for Cyanne L. Tracy.  Prosecuting attorney Jacalyn Christie Labre in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
State moves to delete the second or subsequent enhancers in counts 1 and 2.  It also moves to delete the repeater enhancer in count 3.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea to the amended charge in count 1, possess amphetamine/methamphetamine w/intent.  Convicted.
NO CONTEST plea to the amended charge in count 3, felony bail jumping.  Convicted.
State moves to dismiss and read in counts 4-8.  Motion granted.
Counts 1 and 3 - Sentence withheld and defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety;
4) Comply with all Manitowoc County Drug Court rules and requirements; 
5) Pay court costs;
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) Provide DNA sample
8) AODA assessment. 
9) COUNT 1 ONLY - Spend fourteen (14) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, to commence immediately.
10) COUNT 1 ONLY - Spend an additional three hundred forty six (346) days in the county jail, STAYED and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court.

Count 2 - 
NO CONTEST plea to the amended charge in count 2, possess fentanyl w/intent. 
The Court finds that the defendant freely, voluntarily enters her plea, accepts the plea, finds the defendant guilty and withholds entry of judgment of conviction pursuant to the Deferred Judgment Agreement signed and filed by the parties.
Court will sign approval of Deferred Judgment Agreement once filed by the State.
Deferred judgment agreement (unsigned by the State)
